Subject : Deficient adverse-action notice ( ECOA / FCRA violations ) Citizens Credit Card Services ( Application ID XXXX ) [ Complaint : ] I applied for a Citizens credit card and received an adverse-action notice dated XX/XX/year> that states only : Unable to verify Identity. The notice does not identify any consumer reporting agency or identity-verification vendor, does not explain the specific principal reason ( s ) for the denial, and does not provide the FCRA disclosures required when a consumer report is used. A copy of the denial notice and my certified-mail proof is attached.

] Why I believe this is wrong : ] ECOA/Regulation B requires specific principal reasons for an adverse action or a clear disclosure of the right to request those reasons ( 15 U.S.C. 1691 ( d ) ; 12 C.F.R. 1002.9 ). The statement Unable to verify Identity is vague and non-specific and prevents me from curing or disputing any underlying issue.

If a consumer or identity verification report was used, FCRA 1681m ( a ) requires disclosure of the CRAs name, address, and phone, and notice of the right to obtain a free copy of the report and dispute inaccuracies. The notice I received contains none of these d
